  <scopecontent id="aspace_e44b0b6a21ba801e891dc7601b8c68c6">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Cuneiform tablets (tablets made of clay, stone, metal, or wax, and inscribed with a wedge-shaped stylus) from the Old Babylonian period in ancient Mesopotamia, roughly the site of modern Iraq. Most are records of business transactions.</p>  </scopecontent>
